issue.body:
The change in audio output default device in the system is not reflected inside the electron.

* Electron version: 1.7.x, 1.8.x, 2.0.0-beta.x
* Operating system: Windows 10, Macintosh 
* Devices Used: built-in output device and plantronics c320 usb headset device

### Expected behavior

[Checking the behavior in chrome](https://youtu.be/5qMNrUHNPPE)

The output device value changes with the change in default playback device.

### Actual behavior

[Checking the behavior in electron](https://youtu.be/LxDYWpeZivw)

The output device value doesn't change in electron with the change in default playback device.

### How to reproduce
Try running this following snippet after everytime you set the default output device in the system. This will get the default output device label.

```javascript
navigator
    .mediaDevices
    .enumerateDevices()
    .then( devices => {
        const audioDevices = devices.filter(device => device.kind === 'audiooutput');
        const defaultOuput = audioDevices.find(audio => audio.deviceId == 'default');
        audioDevices.shift();
        const outputDevice = audioDevices.find(audio => defaultOuput.groupId == audio.groupId);
        console.log(outputDevice.label);    
    });
```
